10 An Act relating to agriculture; enacting the Oklahoma
Right to Garden Act of 2025; defining terms;
11 providing the right to grow vegetables in a vegetable
garden for personal consumption; providing that a
12 municipality, city, or town may enact certain
content-neutral ordinances regulating vegetable
13 gardens; providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3031 of Title 2, unless there is
19 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma Right
21 to Garden Act of 2025".
22 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3032 of Title 2, unless there is
24 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
HB1189 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 As used in this act:
2 1. "Residential property" means real property on which there is
3 a dwelling unit with accommodations for four or fewer separate
4 households and is further limited to the primary residence of a
5 person; and
6 2. "Vegetable garden" means a piece of property wholly located
7 within a person's residential property that is used to grow produce,
8 flowers, herbs, fungi, or grains for one's own consumption and
9 enjoyment and not for resale or distribution.
10 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3033 of Title 2, unless there is
12 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. It shall be the right of citizens of the State of Oklahoma
14 to engage in growing their own vegetables in a vegetable garden on
15 their personal property for personal consumption, subject to
16 restrictions rationally related to a governmental purpose.
17 B. Notwithstanding, this section shall not prohibit any
18 municipality, city, or town from enacting content-neutral ordinances
19 or regulations that address the following:
20 1. Limiting the size and proximity of gardens to roadways,
21 structures, or other locations that impact health and safety; or
22 2. The enforcement of constitutional and lawful ordinances
23 adopted by municipalities that are in conformity with general powers
24 of municipal governments within this state that are of a general
HB1189 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.
1 natu re that do not specifically ban gardening, including, but not
2 limited to, regulations and ordinances relating to water usage
3 during drought conditions, fertilizer use, or control of invasive
4 species.
5 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
6
7 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON ENERGY AND NATURAL RESOURCES
OVERSIGHT, dated 03/05/2025 - DO PASS.
